messages.content: What are the two experimental WIP nodes provided by ComfyUI_SeeCoder for ComfyUI?
SEECoderImageEncode and ConcatConditioning are the two experimental WIP nodes provided by ComfyUI_SeeCoder for ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of the SEECoderImageEncode node?
The SEECoderImageEncode node is used to create an embedding from an image.
What inputs are required for the SEECoderImageEncode node?
The SEECoderImageEncode node requires an image to encode and a seecoder_name.
What is the purpose of the ConcatConditioning node?
The ConcatConditioning node is used to concat different embeddings together, allowing the creation of both text and visual embeddings that can be concatenated.
What inputs are required for the ConcatConditioning node?
The ConcatConditioning node requires a set of embeddings to concat something to (conditioning_to) and an embedding to concat behind those (conditioning_from).
Where can the SeeCoders model be found for use with ComfyUI_SeeCoder nodes?
The SeeCoders model can be found on Hugging Face at the following link: https://huggingface.co/shi-labs/prompt-free-diffusion.
Where should the downloaded SeeCoders model be placed in the filesystem for use with ComfyUI_SeeCoder nodes?
The downloaded SeeCoders model should be placed in the `models/seecoders` directory.
What is a future enhancement planned for ComfyUI_SeeCoder?
Future enhancements planned for ComfyUI_SeeCoder include support for non safetensor formats and bringing attention layers in line with those used in ComfyUI.
Are there any specific tasks that ComfyUI_SeeCoder nodes can help with?

Yes, ComfyUI_SeeCoder nodes can help with tasks such as creating embeddings from images and concatenating different embeddings to create a combined representation, which can be useful in various image and text processing applications.
What is the origin of the SeeCoders model?
SeeCoders is developed by SHI-Labs and the model can be found on their GitHub page: https://github.com/SHI-Labs/Prompt-Free-Diffusion.
